<title>MOROCCO: Morocco and France sign nuclear loan accord.</title>
<headline>Morocco and France sign nuclear loan accord.</headline>
<dateline>RABAT 1997-01-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>France signed on Thursday an agreement granting Morocco 520.02 million Francs ($97.9 million) to build a nuclear research centre and to buy nine railway engines, Morocco's finance minister said.</p>
<p>Mohamed Kabbaj outlined the agreement during the signing ceremony attended by French Foreign Trade Minister Yves Galland.</p>
<p>&quot;Morocco is poor in energy resources, it hopes to be able one day to rely on nuclear energy to produce electricity power and even use it for desalination,&quot; said Kabbaj.</p>
<p>The loan is financed partly by the French treasury and a bank consortium led by Societe Generale. (1$ = 5.307 FF)</p>
